iPhone Backup Webapp — Complete Build Prompt
For: Cursor / Claude / Windsurf / v0 / Any AI Code Editor

PROJECT OVERVIEW
Build a local web application (Node.js backend + modern React frontend) that:

Detects and mounts an iPhone on macOS
Detects connected external SSDs
Lets users choose destination folders on the SSD
Copies photos and videos from iPhone to SSD
Tracks every file, skips already-copied files correctly, shows live progress
Handles all interruptions, disconnections, and edge cases gracefully
Is the first module of a larger local photo management system (like a self-hosted Google Photos)


TECH STACK
Backend

Runtime: Node.js 20+ with TypeScript
Framework: Fastify (faster than Express, built-in schema validation)
iPhone mounting: libimobiledevice + ifuse + macFUSE (macOS)
File operations: Node.js fs/promises + streams for large files
Database: SQLite via better-sqlite3 — tracks every file ever seen/copied
Real-time: WebSocket via ws library — live progress to frontend
Process management: execa for running shell commands safely
Media metadata: exiftool (via exiftool-vendored) — reads EXIF date, GPS, dimensions
Checksums: xxhash (fast) for file integrity verification
Queue: p-queue for controlled concurrency

Frontend

Framework: React 18 + Vite
Styling: Tailwind CSS + custom CSS variables for theming
State: Zustand for global state
Real-time: Native WebSocket hook
Animations: Framer Motion
Icons: Lucide React
Charts/progress: Custom SVG components
Font pairing: Syne (display/headings) + DM Sans (body) from Google Fonts

Design Direction
Dark, refined, cinematic. Think: Apple's own design language but warmer — deep charcoal backgrounds (#0f0f0f, #1a1a1a), warm amber/gold accents (#f59e0b) for active states, soft white text (#f0ede8). Clean card-based layout. Subtle grain texture overlay. No gradients on backgrounds — flat dark surfaces with precise borders (1px, rgba white 8%). Progress bars use smooth animated fills. Status indicators pulse gently. The app should feel like a premium local tool, not a website.

